1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:34,040
Chaiya and Manat. I won't mind

2
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:35,760
if you kill them in the process.

3
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:38,120
-Chaiya?
-Puna.

4
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:39,480
<i>Soon,</i>

5
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:41,640
<i>I'll come back and take care of you.</i>

6
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:43,480
I'll never lose to Chaiya!

7
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:46,160
In my life, I'll marry only Puna.

8
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,520
Well, Sonrak

9
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:51,520
wants to marry Puna anyway, doesn't he?

10
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:54,240
Then Puna becomes part of the family.

11
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:56,600
Puna! Puna!

12
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:58,640
PREVIOUS EPISODE

13
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:02,120
<i>Whether they live or die,</i>
<i>it depends on you.</i>

14
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:04,240
I will marry you, Mr. Sonrak.

15
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:07,040
You said it, Puna.

16
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:26,000
Are you Teacher Mueangphrai?

17
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:28,000
-Chaiya!
-I gave this number

18
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:30,760
to Puna. Isn't the phone with her?

19
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:32,720
They took her.

20
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:35,840
The phone fell, so I kept it with me.

21
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,800
Teacher, I just saw the clip

22
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:39,520
of Sonrak proposing to Puna.

23
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:41,160
I saw it too.

24
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:43,120
I honestly don't know what happened.

25
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:45,240
I'm trying to contact Puna right now.

26
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:47,200
Where did they take her?

27
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:49,480
-Do you have any idea?
-Judging from the clip,

28
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:51,880
I think it must be Singha's house.

29
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:52,960
Exactly.

30
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:54,640
I thought the same.

31
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:57,080
Chaiya, how are you now?
You're safe, right?

32
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:58,920
I'm fine. Don't worry, Teacher.

33
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,200
I have to go.

34
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:09,880
Hey!

35
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:14,680
Need any help?

36
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:19,720
No, it's fine. I'll handle this myself.
I can move more freely.

37
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:22,120
Captain, if you want to move freely,

38
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:24,360
I suggest you take my bike.

39
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:26,440
This one.

40
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,160
For your safety.

41
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:33,120
-Thanks a lot, Sergeant.
-Yes.

42
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:06,840
Growing up,

43
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:09,800
I never thought

44
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:14,520
I'd see my parents together.

45
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:28,480
I pray to the sacred spirits.

46
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:31,520
Please protect and watch over

47
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,960
my parents.

48
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:37,000
Please don't let anything happen to them.

49
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:39,360
And let me have the chance

50
00:05:40,720 --> 00:05:43,920
to hug them once more.

51
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,800
Ugh, I'm starving.

52
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:08,000
Me too.

53
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:18,080
Hey, I saw something move.

54
00:07:18,760 --> 00:07:20,800
What moved? Where?

55
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:25,160
What are you two doing?

56
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:26,480
Oh, Aunt Riam.

57
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:29,240
Where are you taking that? Is it mine?

58
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:30,400
No way!

59
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:32,440
It's for Miss Puna.

60
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:36,080
She's not well, her head hurts,
so she asked me to take it upstairs.

61
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:39,440
Auntie, what about our food?

62
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:41,400
Over there, in the kitchen.

63
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:43,400
Do I have to serve it to you too?

64
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:44,920
Ugh, Auntie.

65
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:47,120
Alright, let's go eat in the kitchen.

66
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:04,120
Miss Puna, I put it here for you.

67
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:05,160
Thank you.

68
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:07,600
Do you need anything else?

69
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:10,440
-No, that's all. Thank you so much.
-Sure.

70
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:23,960
Chaiya!

71
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,280
How did you get here?

72
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:35,200
Come with me.

73
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,080
Uh…

74
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,440
Miss Puna!

75
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:50,360
Miss Puna!

76
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:59,880
Miss Puna! I've brought a spoon for you.

77
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:03,040
Miss Puna! Miss Puna!

78
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:05,120
Aunt Riam.

79
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:08,280
-Is something wrong?
-Earlier,

80
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:11,600
I brought her some rice porridge,
but I forgot to bring a spoon,

81
00:09:11,680 --> 00:09:13,320
so I came to give it her.

82
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:17,240
Puna.

83
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:24,400
Puna.

84
00:09:31,920 --> 00:09:32,840
Puna.

85
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:51,400
Let's go.

86
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:09,120
Puna.

87
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:50,440
Hey.

88
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,440
Is that Miss Puna?

89
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:55,600
I don't think so. She's in her room.

90
00:10:58,360 --> 00:10:59,640
Dad!

91
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:02,560
-What is it?
-Puna's not in her room.

92
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:06,640
I just brought her food upstairs,
but when I checked again, she was gone.

93
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:09,320
Tod!

94
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:12,320
-Tod! Tod!
-Yes, Boss!

95
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:13,920
Yes, Boss?

96
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,960
How were you watching Puna?
Do you realize she isn't in her room?

97
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:19,960
Then the person on the motorcycle earlier

98
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:21,600
must have been Miss Puna.

99
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:23,720
What motorcycle? Tell me.

100
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:27,520
I saw Miss Puna
riding on a motorcycle just now.

101
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,720
The driver was a man.

102
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:32,160
Chaiya. It must be Chaiya, Dad.

103
00:11:33,520 --> 00:11:36,000
-Take the car and follow them! Go!
-Yes.

104
00:11:42,880 --> 00:11:46,040
Superintendent, I need your help.

105
00:12:16,280 --> 00:12:18,000
Why did you bring me here?

106
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:24,640
In front of the Buddha,

107
00:12:27,280 --> 00:12:29,480
we'll speak only the truth to each other.

108
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,520
I want to know if you love Sonrak

109
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:38,920
and are willing to marry him.

110
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:41,520
Chaiya.

111
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:43,640
I want you to tell the truth.

112
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:51,160
I don't love him.

113
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:55,320
I never wanted to marry him.

114
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:59,320
Then why? What happened, Puna?

115
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:03,560
Why is there a clip of you
announcing your marriage to him?

116
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:09,720
It was the only condition

117
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:12,720
for me to save my parents.

118
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:17,240
Right now, they've been kidnapped.

119
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:20,800
I don't know if they're alive or dead.

120
00:13:21,680 --> 00:13:23,960
I was afraid that if I refused them…

121
00:13:26,960 --> 00:13:29,040
my parents would be in danger.

122
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:34,840
They promised to bring my parents to me
on the wedding day.

123
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:39,160
I had no other choice.

124
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,760
It was necessary, Chaiya.

125
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:44,640
I promise.

126
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:48,320
Before the wedding,

127
00:13:49,280 --> 00:13:51,760
I'll get your parents out.

128
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:58,080
Do you know where they're being held?

129
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:01,640
I don't know.

130
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:05,600
I really don't.

131
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:08,800
Puna.

132
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:12,760
Let's run away together.

133
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:15,760
Then we'll go back to save your parents.

134
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:20,560
Chaiya.

135
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:24,360
I can't follow my heart.

136
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:30,000
My parents are being held as hostages.

137
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:35,880
Puna.

138
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:40,400
If I disappear,

139
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:44,240
they won't keep my parents alive.

140
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:49,720
I don't want to lose anyone.
I want my parents back.

141
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:02,480
Puna.

142
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,920
I'll trade my life

143
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:09,080
for your parents' lives.

144
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:12,000
No matter what happens tomorrow,

145
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:16,520
let's decide today

146
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:18,640
with our hearts.

147
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:26,800
Puna.

148
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:30,640
Do you love me?

149
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:38,320
I love you, Chaiya.

150
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:41,480
Marry me.

151
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:33,080
In front of the Buddha,

152
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:35,440
I vow

153
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:37,560
to love,

154
00:16:38,880 --> 00:16:41,040
protect, and care for Puna forever.

155
00:16:43,880 --> 00:16:45,520
May this thread

156
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:49,440
symbolize our union,

157
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:52,160
binding us together

158
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,360
with our hearts.

159
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:06,280
I swear before the Buddha

160
00:17:08,440 --> 00:17:10,240
that the man I love

161
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:14,440
is Chaiya.

162
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:21,760
From now on, whatever happens,

163
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:24,640
consider me

164
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:28,280
married to this man.

165
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:58,160
From this moment on, we are a family.

166
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:01,440
I love you, Puna.

167
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:07,720
I love you too, Chaiya.

168
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:32,200
From the blessing thread on our heads,
it's now become a sacred thread.

169
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:36,640
I'll take care of it as best I can.

170
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:39,600
Same here.

171
00:18:41,280 --> 00:18:42,480
I have to go now.

172
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:45,200
I'll go with you.

173
00:18:45,280 --> 00:18:48,120
It's okay. I don't
want you to get into trouble.

174
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:52,800
Split up and find Puna! Go!

175
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:57,080
Go hide quickly! Don't let them see you.

176
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:59,760
I can't. I'm worried about your safety.

177
00:18:59,840 --> 00:19:01,120
I'm fine.

178
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:02,720
Please don't fight.

179
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:06,240
If you do, my parents could be in danger.

180
00:19:06,320 --> 00:19:09,520
Wait until the wedding day,
then we'll deal with them.

181
00:19:10,360 --> 00:19:13,480
Alright, I'll plan to handle them
on the wedding day.

182
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:16,600
-Go quickly!
-Take care of yourself.

183
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:18,920
I'll hurry and find your parents.

184
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:26,120
Hey! There's someone there.

185
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:30,040
Mr. Sonrak.

186
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:31,360
Puna.

187
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:34,280
Puna, how did you get here?

188
00:19:36,080 --> 00:19:38,320
Don't tell me you ran away with Chaiya.

189
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:41,000
Where is he? Where is Chaiya?

190
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,320
-I didn't run away.
-Where is he?

191
00:19:46,080 --> 00:19:47,520
I just came to pray at the temple.

192
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:52,080
Then how did you get here?

193
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:55,520
A motorcycle taxi passed by,
so I hailed it.

194
00:19:56,120 --> 00:19:59,760
-Why didn't you say you were coming?
-I just wanted some time for myself.

195
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:03,280
I've finished praying. Let's go back.

196
00:20:08,120 --> 00:20:09,360
Mr. Sonrak.

197
00:20:11,120 --> 00:20:12,320
Let's go back.

198
00:20:13,840 --> 00:20:15,280
Sorry for making you worry.

199
00:20:22,760 --> 00:20:26,760
Then you have to promise me
that you won't do this again.

200
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:28,760
Okay. Let's go.

201
00:20:31,080 --> 00:20:32,040
Let's go.

202
00:20:58,480 --> 00:21:01,640
Don't move.
There's an order to shoot on sight.

203
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:07,240
But I don't obey that.
I'm just a stubborn cop.

204
00:21:24,320 --> 00:21:25,400
Maria.

205
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:34,640
Hello?

206
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:37,040
Maria, are you safe?

207
00:21:37,120 --> 00:21:38,560
I'm safe. Don't worry.

208
00:21:39,240 --> 00:21:40,560
Where are you now?

209
00:21:40,640 --> 00:21:43,480
I can't say. Dad won't allow it.

210
00:21:43,560 --> 00:21:46,560
I just got my phone fixed,
so I called you right away.

211
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:49,200
You saw the news about me, right?

212
00:21:50,280 --> 00:21:51,800
Are you really a drug dealer?

213
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:53,440
No!

214
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:55,160
I've been framed.

215
00:21:55,760 --> 00:21:58,360
They're after me now,
but I managed to survive.

216
00:21:58,920 --> 00:22:01,320
So you'll always be seen as a criminal?

217
00:22:01,400 --> 00:22:03,560
You can't live
a normal life anymore, right?

218
00:22:04,320 --> 00:22:08,000
The future's uncertain.
I'm sorry it turned out like this.

219
00:22:09,560 --> 00:22:11,560
There's one thing, Maria.

220
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:14,400
The day I dropped you off
at the phone shop,

221
00:22:15,800 --> 00:22:17,400
did I leave a tape behind?

222
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:20,720
I didn't see it.

223
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:22,400
It's an old-style videotape.

224
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:25,920
I must have dropped it at your shop.

225
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:29,320
I really didn't see it.

226
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:31,640
And I can't go back to the shop anymore.

227
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:34,640
They're probably watching.
Dad says it's dangerous.

228
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:36,400
Then where can I find you?

229
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,840
You can't. Dad won't let me say anything.

230
00:22:41,240 --> 00:22:43,240
That's it for now.
I'm turning off my phone.

231
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:55,160
Why did you lie about the tape?

232
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:58,120
Dad, we don't even know the truth yet.

233
00:22:58,200 --> 00:23:01,960
If we said we had the tape,
arranged to hand it over,

234
00:23:02,040 --> 00:23:05,200
and someone followed us to kill us,
it would be dangerous.

235
00:23:06,320 --> 00:23:07,440
That's true.

236
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:10,440
It's better not to say anything.

237
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:31,040
-Sonrak.
-Yes.

238
00:23:31,120 --> 00:23:33,520
Go get something for Puna to drink.

239
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:34,680
Got it.

240
00:23:40,800 --> 00:23:41,760
What are you planning?

241
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:46,040
Don't forget, your parents' lives
are in my hands.

242
00:23:49,920 --> 00:23:50,920
Yes.

243
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:52,840
I won't forget.

244
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:57,360
Also, behave properly around Sonrak.

245
00:23:57,440 --> 00:23:59,440
Don't make him uncomfortable.

246
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:05,800
And the deal between us,

247
00:24:06,840 --> 00:24:08,720
make sure Sonrak never finds out.

248
00:24:11,120 --> 00:24:13,360
If he does, I'll consider you
in breach of the deal.

249
00:24:15,560 --> 00:24:16,920
Here's your water.

250
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:24,080
-Dad, is something wrong?
-Nothing.

251
00:24:24,720 --> 00:24:25,920
I was just talking to Puna.

252
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:28,800
In the old days, people believed
someone about to marry

253
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:31,200
shouldn't go out alone.

254
00:24:32,120 --> 00:24:33,560
Have you heard of that, Puna?

255
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:37,000
Yes, I have. Thank you for the warning.

256
00:24:48,640 --> 00:24:51,000
DARATHONG MUSIC

257
00:24:55,800 --> 00:24:58,360
Mr. Singha, Ms. Praewa is here.

258
00:24:59,320 --> 00:25:00,760
Have her come in.

259
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:08,320
-Hello, Mr. Singha.
-Please have a seat.

260
00:25:12,120 --> 00:25:15,280
I'm sorry for the sudden appointment.
I didn't notify you in advance.

261
00:25:16,600 --> 00:25:19,440
How can our record label assist you?

262
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:21,640
Please don't say it like that.

263
00:25:21,720 --> 00:25:25,280
It should be me serving you, Mr. Singha.

264
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:29,520
Well, I heard the news

265
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:31,680
that Mr. Sonrak and Ms. Puna
are getting married,

266
00:25:31,760 --> 00:25:35,520
so I wanted to offer my help
with the wedding.

267
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:37,800
That's right.

268
00:25:37,880 --> 00:25:40,560
Your company specializes
in event planning.

269
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:42,880
You must be very experienced
with weddings.

270
00:25:43,520 --> 00:25:47,120
Yes. I've arranged weddings
for many couples in the industry.

271
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:50,800
I'm also a fan of Mr. Sonrak and Ms. Puna,

272
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:52,200
so I'd love to help.

273
00:25:52,280 --> 00:25:53,840
Alright, let's do it.

274
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:56,160
I'm looking for someone
to organize the wedding anyway.

275
00:25:56,840 --> 00:26:00,880
How about I arrange for you
to meet Sonrak and Puna?

276
00:26:00,960 --> 00:26:02,160
When should we do it?

277
00:26:02,880 --> 00:26:06,000
Today, please. Since time is short,

278
00:26:06,080 --> 00:26:07,800
we'll need time to get everything ready.

279
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:11,240
Okay. Wait a moment.

280
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:18,840
Sonrak?

281
00:26:19,360 --> 00:26:21,640
I'll have someone from the event company

282
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:24,440
come in to talk about your wedding.

283
00:26:24,520 --> 00:26:25,680
It's today.

284
00:26:25,760 --> 00:26:26,920
Alright.

285
00:26:29,080 --> 00:26:30,160
Done.

286
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:39,520
DARATHONG MUSIC

287
00:26:57,400 --> 00:26:59,080
Oh, Praewa's calling.

288
00:27:01,480 --> 00:27:02,560
<i>Hello.</i>

289
00:27:03,840 --> 00:27:05,280
Praewa, how's it going?

290
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:07,680
Don't try to sound sweet.

291
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:10,240
I just wanted to call
and say the plan worked.

292
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:11,960
Really?

293
00:27:13,120 --> 00:27:15,160
Today you'll get to see Puna, right?

294
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:18,840
<i>Yes. They've scheduled a discussion</i>
<i>about the wedding at home,</i>

295
00:27:18,920 --> 00:27:20,360
<i>and I'll take care of the rest.</i>

296
00:27:21,800 --> 00:27:24,520
You're the sweetest. I miss you.

297
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:27,080
Yeah!

298
00:27:36,240 --> 00:27:37,960
It worked, everyone.

299
00:27:38,560 --> 00:27:41,800
Praewa is about to meet Puna.

300
00:27:42,920 --> 00:27:44,560
What about the thing we left with her?

301
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:49,120
Don't worry, she'll handle it perfectly.
I know her well.

302
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:50,600
Good.

303
00:27:50,680 --> 00:27:52,880
The most important thing right now is

304
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:56,480
we have to save Puna's parents,
who were taken by Singha.

305
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:12,800
With this theme,
the wedding will look beautiful.

306
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:16,320
Sure. I have full confidence in you.

307
00:28:16,960 --> 00:28:18,080
Perfect!

308
00:28:19,600 --> 00:28:20,680
Let's go with this plan.

309
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:23,720
Sure, anything is fine.

310
00:28:28,760 --> 00:28:31,600
Oh, I'm so hungry.

311
00:28:31,680 --> 00:28:34,400
Can I have some snacks?

312
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:36,880
Of course. Aunt Riam!

313
00:28:38,280 --> 00:28:39,360
Aunt Riam!

314
00:28:40,200 --> 00:28:42,520
I'll go get something for you.
Wait a moment.

315
00:28:43,600 --> 00:28:44,760
Thank you.

316
00:28:57,280 --> 00:28:58,600
Puna, take this.

317
00:28:59,800 --> 00:29:01,600
This is from Chaiya.

318
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:09,040
What is it?

319
00:29:09,920 --> 00:29:11,640
A GPS tracker.

320
00:29:15,120 --> 00:29:17,840
Wait, what's the plan?

321
00:29:36,440 --> 00:29:37,800
Stop!

322
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:41,880
Stop! Your hands are all cut up.

323
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:45,560
No, Wilai. I can't stop!

324
00:29:46,760 --> 00:29:48,600
I promised Thip

325
00:29:48,680 --> 00:29:50,240
that I'd never abandon Puna.

326
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:53,920
Even if she's not my biological daughter,

327
00:29:54,640 --> 00:29:57,320
I'll never ever abandon her.

328
00:29:57,400 --> 00:29:58,760
-Damn it!
-Stop!

329
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:04,960
Trying to escape?

330
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:08,240
There's no way you're getting out of here.

331
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:16,880
Stop right now! Listen to me!

332
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:20,960
What is it?

333
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:26,600
Whether you're Phupha or Tharin,

334
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:29,120
the time has come

335
00:30:30,160 --> 00:30:32,200
for me to tell you the truth.

336
00:30:35,640 --> 00:30:36,880
What truth?

337
00:30:39,600 --> 00:30:41,400
The truth about Onanong,

338
00:30:42,080 --> 00:30:45,160
Phupha, and Puna.

339
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:55,440
<i>Still waiting</i>

340
00:30:56,280 --> 00:31:01,680
<i>I kept hoping until I grew weary</i>

341
00:31:03,840 --> 00:31:04,800
Are you pregnant?

342
00:31:04,880 --> 00:31:08,520
I just found out when I came to Bangkok.

343
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:09,840
You know

344
00:31:10,560 --> 00:31:12,240
what has to be done about this.

345
00:31:12,320 --> 00:31:14,400
Please let me keep this child.

346
00:31:15,480 --> 00:31:18,560
I promise I won't let anyone know.

347
00:31:19,160 --> 00:31:20,640
This is your father, my dear.

348
00:31:21,360 --> 00:31:23,840
Your father's name is Phupha.

349
00:31:23,920 --> 00:31:26,920
I love your father very much.

350
00:31:28,920 --> 00:31:31,280
-On.
-Hey, Thip.

351
00:31:35,520 --> 00:31:37,200
How is Phupha?

352
00:31:37,280 --> 00:31:40,840
Since you left him,
he's been really heartbroken.

353
00:31:41,640 --> 00:31:42,840
He misunderstood.

354
00:31:42,920 --> 00:31:46,440
He thought you left
because he had no future.

355
00:31:46,520 --> 00:31:48,400
Now, everyone

356
00:31:48,480 --> 00:31:49,600
thinks you wanted

357
00:31:49,680 --> 00:31:51,520
to be a singer and become famous,

358
00:31:51,600 --> 00:31:53,840
so you left him and ran to Bangkok.

359
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:56,440
Did he suspect anything
about the baby in my womb?

360
00:31:57,320 --> 00:31:58,960
Not at all.

361
00:31:59,040 --> 00:32:02,040
He didn't even realize
you were pregnant with his child.

362
00:32:02,120 --> 00:32:03,680
Then don't tell him yet.

363
00:32:03,760 --> 00:32:07,040
I want to become famous
and make a lot of money.

364
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:10,760
So I can use that money
to buy back his land.

365
00:32:10,840 --> 00:32:13,200
You're letting everyone misunderstand you,

366
00:32:13,280 --> 00:32:14,880
just to help the one you love.

367
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:19,320
Namthip, give this money to Phupha.

368
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:21,000
For what?

369
00:32:23,640 --> 00:32:25,600
When I ran away to Bangkok,

370
00:32:26,520 --> 00:32:28,440
Phupha mortgaged his farmland

371
00:32:28,520 --> 00:32:30,400
to pay for his mother's treatment.

372
00:32:30,480 --> 00:32:32,720
If he doesn't have the money
to redeem it yet,

373
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:35,400
give it to him.

374
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:39,520
Okay. But will he take it?

375
00:32:39,600 --> 00:32:42,200
Right now, he misunderstands.

376
00:32:42,280 --> 00:32:44,840
He thinks you left him because he's poor.

377
00:32:45,360 --> 00:32:46,680
He probably won't accept your money.

378
00:32:46,760 --> 00:32:48,360
Then tell him it's your money.

379
00:32:49,320 --> 00:32:50,520
Say you're lending it to him

380
00:32:50,600 --> 00:32:52,520
to save the land.

381
00:32:53,400 --> 00:32:54,600
But the most important thing,

382
00:32:55,160 --> 00:32:57,560
you must keep it a secret about Puna.

383
00:32:57,640 --> 00:32:59,480
Don't let him know

384
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:00,960
she's our child.

385
00:33:01,600 --> 00:33:03,560
Otherwise, everything will be ruined.

386
00:33:04,680 --> 00:33:06,120
Got it.

387
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:08,880
I'll tell everyone that Puna is my child.

388
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:11,680
No one will suspect a thing.

389
00:33:13,520 --> 00:33:17,320
I promise. Only you and I
will know about this.

390
00:33:22,480 --> 00:33:23,720
Thip.

391
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:25,960
I know

392
00:33:26,960 --> 00:33:28,200
you love Phupha too.

393
00:33:34,440 --> 00:33:36,080
-On.
-If Phupha ever loves again,

394
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:39,760
I want him to open his heart to you.

395
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:43,920
It would be good

396
00:33:44,640 --> 00:33:47,080
if you and he could end up together

397
00:33:48,760 --> 00:33:50,200
and have Puna as your child.

398
00:33:52,160 --> 00:33:53,640
No.

399
00:33:53,720 --> 00:33:57,040
You and Phupha must be together.
One day, you'll be.

400
00:33:58,560 --> 00:34:00,200
That's impossible, Thip.

401
00:34:02,240 --> 00:34:03,840
I'm a singer now.

402
00:34:05,800 --> 00:34:07,440
I've come too far…

403
00:34:09,040 --> 00:34:10,480
to go back.

404
00:34:11,520 --> 00:34:13,880
I've gone too far.
There's no turning back.

405
00:34:15,639 --> 00:34:16,760
Go, Thip.

406
00:34:17,800 --> 00:34:19,400
Take Puna to Phupha.

407
00:34:21,440 --> 00:34:23,760
Please make her your child too.

408
00:34:26,400 --> 00:34:27,239
It's time, my dear.

409
00:34:33,440 --> 00:34:34,480
Okay.

410
00:34:34,560 --> 00:34:38,000
I promise I'll take care
of Puna as best as I can.

411
00:34:39,080 --> 00:34:41,040
I'll be her mother.

412
00:34:41,679 --> 00:34:44,719
I'll love her like any mother would.

413
00:34:48,040 --> 00:34:49,159
Thank you, my friend.

414
00:34:49,719 --> 00:34:51,000
Thank you so much.

415
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:11,360
On.

416
00:35:12,960 --> 00:35:15,200
-On.
-Yes.

417
00:35:18,880 --> 00:35:20,040
Puna.

418
00:35:22,680 --> 00:35:24,240
Is Puna really my child?

419
00:35:25,680 --> 00:35:26,840
Yes.

420
00:35:28,040 --> 00:35:31,080
-Puna really is my child?
-Yes.

421
00:35:32,480 --> 00:35:33,480
Puna.

422
00:35:35,640 --> 00:35:37,640
Puna is your child.

423
00:35:37,720 --> 00:35:39,680
-Phupha.
-Puna.

424
00:35:43,240 --> 00:35:44,640
Right now,

425
00:35:45,240 --> 00:35:47,520
death is so close to us.

426
00:35:48,200 --> 00:35:51,160
I don't want to hide this anymore.

427
00:35:52,480 --> 00:35:56,600
And you shouldn't hide
who you are either, Phupha.

428
00:36:03,760 --> 00:36:06,200
I'm sorry.

429
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:08,920
Sorry for abandoning you.

430
00:36:09,720 --> 00:36:11,800
Sorry for hiding the truth
about our child.

431
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:16,080
Sorry for letting things
turn out like this.

432
00:36:17,080 --> 00:36:18,520
No, On.

433
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:24,400
You don't have to apologize.
You haven't done anything wrong.

434
00:36:26,320 --> 00:36:28,080
Everything you've done

435
00:36:28,160 --> 00:36:30,680
has been right, from that day until now.

436
00:36:31,520 --> 00:36:32,680
I'm the one…

437
00:36:34,120 --> 00:36:35,320
who should reflect

438
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:38,680
on how much you've sacrificed for me.

439
00:36:43,120 --> 00:36:46,120
Thank you, On. Thank you for everything.

440
00:37:03,880 --> 00:37:06,000
We have to help our daughter.

441
00:37:06,080 --> 00:37:08,280
I promise.

442
00:37:18,480 --> 00:37:19,600
Hello.

443
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:22,720
What is it?

444
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:26,760
Khod?

445
00:37:29,040 --> 00:37:30,360
And what did he say?

446
00:37:53,520 --> 00:37:54,720
What's up, Kitti?

447
00:37:55,640 --> 00:37:59,160
Chart just called about Boss Noo.

448
00:37:59,920 --> 00:38:01,400
He's still not dead?

449
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:03,880
Khod said right now,

450
00:38:04,760 --> 00:38:08,600
Boss Noo is running to get help
from the 14K mafia.

451
00:38:10,120 --> 00:38:13,720
-Huh? 14K?
-<i>Yes.</i>

452
00:38:14,520 --> 00:38:15,640
14K.

453
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:18,600
They're coming to help
Boss Noo get revenge.

454
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:21,040
But don't worry.

455
00:38:22,280 --> 00:38:24,840
I know some of the mafia guys myself.

456
00:38:30,280 --> 00:38:33,080
Kitti, help me out.

457
00:38:33,160 --> 00:38:35,160
Get someone to deal with Boss Noo.

458
00:38:35,240 --> 00:38:37,000
I'm fed up with him.

459
00:38:39,960 --> 00:38:41,000
Got it.

460
00:38:41,760 --> 00:38:43,080
Then,

461
00:38:43,880 --> 00:38:45,640
let's meet up, alright?

462
00:38:46,560 --> 00:38:49,400
Fine, I'll meet you at the safe house.

463
00:38:49,480 --> 00:38:50,840
Wait for me a moment.

464
00:39:03,240 --> 00:39:04,480
Puna.

465
00:39:07,320 --> 00:39:10,920
Why were you eavesdropping
on my dad's call?

466
00:39:19,560 --> 00:39:20,400
Puna.

467
00:39:21,920 --> 00:39:25,120
I saw you standing there
listening to him for a long time.

468
00:39:27,680 --> 00:39:29,000
What are you doing?

469
00:39:30,560 --> 00:39:31,960
I was…

470
00:39:34,480 --> 00:39:36,920
Why are you doing this, Puna?
Is something wrong?

471
00:39:41,440 --> 00:39:42,360
Is everything okay?

472
00:39:47,200 --> 00:39:48,240
Puna.

473
00:39:49,440 --> 00:39:53,080
You can talk to me about anything, okay?

474
00:39:55,120 --> 00:39:56,760
Did my dad force you

475
00:39:57,560 --> 00:39:59,320
or do anything bad to you?

476
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:08,440
No.

477
00:40:09,760 --> 00:40:13,040
Your dad's been kind to me.

478
00:40:13,760 --> 00:40:15,960
He hasn't forced me at all.

479
00:40:20,520 --> 00:40:23,480
You really want to marry me, right?

480
00:40:32,520 --> 00:40:33,640
Yes.

481
00:40:35,040 --> 00:40:37,240
I want to marry you.

482
00:40:41,520 --> 00:40:43,920
You want to marry me,
so why are you crying, Puna?

483
00:40:44,880 --> 00:40:48,360
You should be happy! Don't cry.

484
00:40:49,640 --> 00:40:51,640
I'm crying because I'm happy.

485
00:40:53,200 --> 00:40:54,400
Really happy.

486
00:41:21,280 --> 00:41:23,600
-I'm going outside for a bit.
-Yes, Dad.

487
00:41:24,320 --> 00:41:26,440
I'm counting on you
to look after the house,

488
00:41:27,200 --> 00:41:29,520
and take good care of your bride-to-be.

489
00:41:31,680 --> 00:41:32,720
Yes, Dad.

490
00:41:44,760 --> 00:41:46,440
Come on, let's see Dad out.

491
00:41:47,040 --> 00:41:48,040
Let's go.

492
00:42:01,080 --> 00:42:02,520
-You all follow along.
-Yes.

493
00:43:15,320 --> 00:43:17,360
The GPS has moved away
from Singha's house.

494
00:43:18,840 --> 00:43:20,240
Send this info to Captain Tom.

495
00:43:21,200 --> 00:43:22,440
On it, buddy.

496
00:43:36,320 --> 00:43:39,440
-Singha, where are you?
-Almost there.

497
00:43:39,520 --> 00:43:42,160
Hey, cancel it. Don't come.

498
00:43:43,280 --> 00:43:45,840
Khod just reported
that Boss Noo and his gang

499
00:43:45,920 --> 00:43:48,040
have already entered the area.

500
00:43:48,120 --> 00:43:49,760
Why are you only telling me now?

501
00:44:00,120 --> 00:44:02,400
-Singha!
-Boss Noo! Hey, stop the car!

502
00:44:04,360 --> 00:44:05,840
Chit, go deal with him!

503
00:44:25,880 --> 00:44:27,240
Who's with Boss Noo?

504
00:44:29,640 --> 00:44:31,040
The 14K mafia.

505
00:44:32,160 --> 00:44:36,240
This time, we'll just watch from the hill.
Let the tigers fight it out.

506
00:44:37,160 --> 00:44:39,400
Perfect. Less work for us.

507
00:44:42,320 --> 00:44:44,880
-Where's Captain Tom now?
-On his way.

508
00:44:51,640 --> 00:44:54,640
Chit! Go back now!

509
00:45:02,040 --> 00:45:03,160
Hurry up!

510
00:45:27,640 --> 00:45:29,120
Singha is heading this way.

511
00:45:32,280 --> 00:45:33,600
His destination must be around there.

512
00:45:36,640 --> 00:45:37,880
There's a suspicious house here.

513
00:45:46,160 --> 00:45:47,360
Where are you, Captain?

514
00:45:47,440 --> 00:45:49,400
I'm near the spot
where the clash is happening.

515
00:45:49,480 --> 00:45:50,880
Then take another route.

516
00:45:52,000 --> 00:45:54,240
I'll send you the location.
We'll meet there.

517
00:45:55,200 --> 00:45:56,480
<i>Got it.</i>

518
00:45:58,080 --> 00:45:59,000
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

519
00:46:20,040 --> 00:46:22,560
Boss, someone saw Singha's car
being shot at,

520
00:46:22,640 --> 00:46:24,280
but he managed to escape.

521
00:46:25,040 --> 00:46:27,600
-Do you know who they were?
-Boss Noo's gang, sir.

522
00:46:28,520 --> 00:46:29,720
I knew it.

523
00:46:40,040 --> 00:46:41,840
Stop! Police!

524
00:46:42,880 --> 00:46:43,920
The cops are here! Take cover!

525
00:47:03,360 --> 00:47:04,320
Take him out!

526
00:47:31,000 --> 00:47:32,480
Hey! Watch out for the grenade!

527
00:47:50,440 --> 00:47:51,960
My dad worked so hard

528
00:47:52,040 --> 00:47:54,840
to provide for my mom and me,

529
00:47:54,920 --> 00:47:56,480
so we could have a good life.

530
00:47:56,560 --> 00:47:59,360
Are you sure your father

531
00:47:59,440 --> 00:48:01,920
has lived up
to being worthy of admiration?

532
00:48:02,000 --> 00:48:03,320
Tell her to kneel and apologize to me!

533
00:48:03,960 --> 00:48:06,240
I will never apologize
to someone who breaks the law.

534
00:48:06,320 --> 00:48:07,520
NEXT EPISODE

535
00:48:07,600 --> 00:48:08,720
Stop talking nonsense!

536
00:48:08,800 --> 00:48:10,640
Puna isn't talking nonsense.

537
00:48:10,720 --> 00:48:12,120
You're slandering my dad!

538
00:48:12,200 --> 00:48:14,040
If you want to stop me from doing my job,

539
00:48:15,280 --> 00:48:16,160
go ahead.

540
00:48:16,240 --> 00:48:17,240
You're dead!

541
00:51:16,000 --> 00:51:19,360
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
